{{!--
    Automated-combat attack card BODY (spoken by the attacker).

    Body only — the four defense buttons are appended by `buildActionCard` from
    the `buttons` array in the card's ActionCardSpec (see `buildAttackCardData`),
    so they are not written here. Each defense button carries the evaluated
    AttackResult in its `data-scope` (revived as `context.scope.attackResult`) and
    is addressed to the defender's combatant; per-defender capability gating
    happens at render time in `gateAutomatedDefenseButtons`.

    Transparency-by-design: the attacker's Aim and Aspect choices and the
    resolved Attack Mastery Level are shown so every player can verify the
    parameters of the attack.
--}}
<div class="hmk chat-card item-card" data-actor-id="{{actorId}}">
    <header class="card-header">
        <h3 class="title">{{title}}</h3>
        <h4 class="subtitle">{{attackerName}} vs. {{defenderName}}</h4>
    </header>

    <div class="grid grid-2col">
        <div class="card-content">
            <span class="label">Aim:</span>
            <span class="value">{{aimLabel}}</span>
        </div>

        <div class="card-content">
            <span class="label">Aspect:</span>
            <span class="value">{{aspect}}</span>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card-content center">
        <span class="label">AML:</span>
        <span class="value">{{aml}}</span>
    </div>
</div>
